g controversies and contradictions of Black Studies and feminism at San Francisco State University. Smith also locates his story in the context of the scholarly literature on African American politics, imbuing it with his own personal perspective. His account illuminates the past but, at the same time, looks toward the future of the long struggle by African American scholars to use knowledge as a base of power in the fight against racism and white supremacy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aAfrican American scholarszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aAfrican American teacherszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aCollege teacherszUnited StatesvBiography. 4aAfrican American Studies : African American Studies. 4aGeneral Interest : Autobiography, Biography and Memoir. 4aHistory : American History. 4aHistory : Intellectual History. 4aPolitics and Law : American Politics. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Educators.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2021z978311149169140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143848233040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438482330423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438482330/original  a978-3-11-149169-1  SUNY Press eBook Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles